                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.348 Z 4/139: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kellogg</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-02-13T13:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1924—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. My 434, October 11, 4 p.m.,<note n="93" xml:id="d131fn93">“Your unnumbered
                        instruction September 18. The Foreign Office desires to know whether <hi
                            rend="italic">ZR–3</hi> will be delivered to the United States in
                        Germany or in America. Harvey.” (File no. 811.348 Z 4/50.)</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">re</hi> flight of airship <hi rend="italic">ZR</hi> [–<hi
                        rend="italic">3</hi>]. Foreign Office desires to know nationality and
                    ownership of airship and [<hi rend="italic">at?</hi>] the time of her flight
                    from Friedrichshafen to the United States and whether she is to be considered a
                    civil or military airship.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
